WEBVTT

00:01.186 --> 00:12.923
Today, we get to discuss together the most momentous statement in all the Bible.

00:14.586 --> 00:15.687
Now, that's a pretty big claim.

00:17.170 --> 00:20.154
There's lots of important statements in the Bible.

00:20.234 --> 00:25.522
Obviously, everything's important, but there's genealogies and other things where you're like, oh, yeah, okay, that's fine.

00:26.146 --> 00:33.375
But there's a lot of passages where you're like, man, that's my life verse, or that is super powerful, or that changed my life.

00:34.297 --> 00:36.459
I'm not in any way negating any of that.

00:38.502 --> 00:48.395
But this morning, we're gonna look at what I believe is the most momentous statement in all the Bible.

00:50.177 --> 00:54.002
In 20 years of preaching at Calvary Church, I've not been able to make that claim.

00:55.202 --> 00:56.384
I'm making it this morning.

00:57.886 --> 01:03.916
So let me invite you to take a Bible and turn to the book of 1 John 4.

01:04.256 --> 01:09.104
First John 4, maybe you're visiting here and you don't have a Bible with you.

01:09.124 --> 01:10.687
There's one in the rack in front of you.

01:11.588 --> 01:20.402
And hopefully we've piqued your interest to say, wow, this is a big book, but I'm going to tell you the most momentous statement in all the Bible.

01:21.762 --> 01:24.666
Maybe you're willing to follow along and just see it for yourselves.

01:24.867 --> 01:26.709
Well, in the church Bibles, it's page 988.

01:27.070 --> 01:31.236
That's 1 John chapter 4.

01:34.061 --> 01:42.453
And again, funnily enough, just kind of the way Lord works, you might think the most momentous statement in the Bible would be on page 1 or on the last page.

01:43.595 --> 01:48.242
Here it is, tucked away in this little letter near the end of the Bible.

01:49.602 --> 01:56.128
Now when I say the most momentous statement, I don't mean the most foundational.

01:57.489 --> 02:01.553
If you ask me, what is the most foundational truth in the Bible?

02:01.613 --> 02:05.958
What is the thing, the truth that everything else is built on?

02:07.359 --> 02:09.641
It's that Jesus is Lord.

02:11.002 --> 02:14.686
That is the foundation upon which everything else is built.

02:16.528 --> 02:19.090
This morning we're going to see a different

02:19.426 --> 02:21.088
sentence.

02:21.108 --> 02:39.315
This sentence is not the most foundational, but I believe it is the most momentous, the most earth-shattering, the most powerful, the most definitive statement of who God is, and it's in our passage in 1 John chapter 4.

02:40.217 --> 02:46.546
Now I'm going to read for us verses 7 to 21, but let me just explain how this passage works.

02:46.946 --> 02:50.890
It's a really, really powerful, deep and important passage.

02:50.910 --> 02:53.412
And we can't cover it in one week.

02:53.432 --> 02:57.236
So we're going to spend three weeks on this passage.

02:57.256 --> 03:01.740
But the passage doesn't break up nicely into three distinct sections.

03:02.341 --> 03:09.288
So we're kind of covering this whole section three times, pulling out three different things.

03:09.688 --> 03:15.634
So we'll be back in this passage next week as we celebrate Christmas next Sunday morning.

03:16.194 --> 03:22.102
But this morning, we're going to hear the most momentous statement in all the Bible.

03:22.723 --> 03:25.046
I'm going to read the whole passage and then we're going to talk about it.

03:25.427 --> 03:29.873
1 John 4 page 988 verses 7 to 21.

03:34.039 --> 03:39.346
Dear friends, let us love one another for love comes from God.

03:41.068 --> 03:45.074
Everyone who loves has been born of God and knows God.

03:46.114 --> 03:50.899
Whoever does not love does not know God because God is love.

03:52.500 --> 03:55.143
This is how God showed his love among us.

03:56.264 --> 04:02.570
He sent his one and only son into the world that we might live through him.

04:04.492 --> 04:14.482
This is love not that we loved God, but that he loved us and sent his son as an atoning sacrifice for our sins.

04:16.066 --> 04:22.557
dear friends, since God so loved us, we also ought to love one another.

04:24.079 --> 04:32.233
No one has seen God, but if we love one another, God lives in us and His love is made complete in us.

04:33.495 --> 04:37.341
This is how we know that we live in Him and He in us.

04:38.183 --> 04:40.146
He has given us of His Spirit.

04:41.314 --> 04:48.902
And we have seen and testified that the Father has sent His Son to be the Savior of the world.

04:50.304 --> 04:56.270
If anyone acknowledges that Jesus is the Son of God, God lives in them and they in God.

04:57.331 --> 05:01.776
And so we know and rely on the love God has for us.

05:03.418 --> 05:06.181
God is love.

05:07.663 --> 05:10.866
Whoever lives in love lives in God and God in them.

05:11.874 --> 05:18.102
This is how love is made complete among us so that we will have confidence on the day of judgment.

05:18.883 --> 05:20.745
In this world, we are like Jesus.

05:21.907 --> 05:29.696
There is no fear in love, but perfect love drives out fear because fear has to do with punishment.

05:30.517 --> 05:33.501
The one who fears is not made perfect in love.

05:35.303 --> 05:37.406
We love because he first loved us.

05:38.688 --> 05:40.690
Whoever claims to love God

05:40.834 --> 05:50.929
yet hates a brother or sister is a liar, for whoever does not love their brother and sister whom they have seen cannot love God whom they have not seen.

05:52.151 --> 05:59.742
And he has given us this command, anyone who loves God must also love their brother and sister.

06:02.106 --> 06:10.258
In all of the Bible, we get occasionally a construction

06:11.106 --> 06:15.871
that draws attention grammatically to something very powerful.

06:17.413 --> 06:33.731
Four times in the Bible, we have a construction where God is the subject of the sentence, followed by a stative verb, a linking verb, a helping verb like is, and then followed by a noun.

06:35.573 --> 06:40.498
Now we have lots of constructions where we have God is and then followed by an adjective.

06:40.962 --> 06:41.843
God is holy.

06:42.484 --> 06:43.606
God is compassionate.

06:44.187 --> 06:45.168
God is kind.

06:45.709 --> 06:46.730
God is just.

06:47.371 --> 06:49.655
Holy, compassionate, just, faithful.

06:49.695 --> 06:50.796
Those are adjectives.

06:51.357 --> 06:56.044
And that's powerful, but that's simply describing who God is.

06:57.125 --> 07:00.410
For example, if I said to you, Lisa is beautiful.

07:01.251 --> 07:03.034
That's an adjective describing Lisa.

07:04.376 --> 07:08.562
But if I said Lisa is beauty itself,

07:09.410 --> 07:11.273
Well, that's a pretty powerful statement.

07:12.055 --> 07:18.065
That is a definitive statement to follow the verb is with the noun is a big deal.

07:19.628 --> 07:23.696
Four times in the whole Bible, we have a construction.

07:23.876 --> 07:29.045
God is followed not by an adjective, but by a noun.

07:31.089 --> 07:34.034
And all four of them are given to us by the Apostle John.

07:35.906 --> 07:47.640
John wrote a gospel and in John chapter four of that gospel, he tells us God is spirit, not spiritual, that would be an adjective.

07:48.421 --> 07:50.304
God is spirit.

07:51.145 --> 07:55.410
It's a definitive declaration that God is spirit.

07:57.272 --> 08:01.417
And first John chapter one, John gives us the second of the four.

08:03.079 --> 08:05.362
He says, God is

08:05.730 --> 08:21.635
light, not just that God is pure or that God is life giving, but that light as a noun actually defines who God is in his essence.

08:25.201 --> 08:33.234
And then in our passage, John gives us this construction with a third noun.

08:34.722 --> 08:36.124
but He gives it to us twice.

08:38.026 --> 08:43.634
In our passage, it is declared for us under inspiration of the Spirit.

08:45.116 --> 08:48.961
God is love.

08:51.985 --> 09:01.618
Of these four powerful definitive statements, God is love is told us twice.

09:02.626 --> 09:07.693
That's why I think this is the most momentous statement in the Bible.

09:09.515 --> 09:10.957
Lots of important statements.

09:12.699 --> 09:29.141
But if you were only given three words, if you only had three last breaths before your life was over, if you had only the chance to tell somebody in three words, who is God?

09:30.203 --> 09:32.626
These are your words.

09:33.794 --> 09:34.255
God is love.

09:35.817 --> 09:36.458
God is love.

09:38.340 --> 09:46.292
Because this is so momentous, we want to spend some time this morning unpacking.

09:47.173 --> 09:49.917
What does it mean that God is love?

09:51.078 --> 09:54.784
Why does God reveal Himself to us this way?

09:55.204 --> 09:59.410
God is spirit, God is light, and God is love, and God is love.

10:03.138 --> 10:10.185
First of all, it's important to note that we are not talking about an attribute of God when we say God is love.

10:11.506 --> 10:15.149
We are talking about the essence of who God is.

10:15.570 --> 10:20.474
This is a definitive statement, not a descriptive statement.

10:21.355 --> 10:21.916
What does that mean?

10:21.956 --> 10:24.198
Let me give you a couple of examples that might have explained this.

10:25.739 --> 10:27.481
Many of you in the room have a cell phone.

10:28.862 --> 10:32.626
If I asked you to pull out your phone and you looked at the home screen,

10:32.866 --> 10:37.111
You would see on your cell phone similar things to what I see on my cell phone, which is a lot of apps.

10:38.112 --> 10:40.855
You might have an app for surfing the web.

10:40.875 --> 10:44.019
You might have an app for navigating with maps.

10:44.059 --> 10:48.784
You might have an app for telling you what the weather is, which you don't need an app to tell you it's super cold outside.

10:49.785 --> 10:52.148
You might have an app for video games to play on your phone.

10:52.168 --> 10:54.611
You might have an app to help you find a parking spot.

10:54.631 --> 10:56.333
Our phones have a lot of apps on them.

10:56.373 --> 11:00.658
And what the apps do is they describe, really, what the phone does.

11:01.186 --> 11:05.433
Because I have a weather app, I can tell what the weather is with my phone.

11:06.194 --> 11:14.286
Because I have a navigation app, I can find a place because my phone is able to help me find that because I have that app.

11:14.306 --> 11:18.233
Because I have a parking app, I can pay for a parking space through my phone.

11:18.513 --> 11:21.818
The apps describe what the phone does.

11:24.122 --> 11:25.904
These are like God's attributes.

11:28.008 --> 11:29.490
We say God is wise.

11:30.018 --> 11:33.282
That means that when you interact with God, what you get from God is wisdom.

11:34.624 --> 11:36.326
We say that God is kind.

11:37.027 --> 11:41.032
That means when God does something for us, we receive kindness from God.

11:41.312 --> 11:43.055
We say God is just.

11:43.856 --> 11:45.197
Again, these are all adjectives.

11:46.179 --> 11:51.706
That means that anything God does, any decision he makes is right and holy and good.

11:55.150 --> 11:58.194
But when I describe that box that you hold in your hand,

11:59.714 --> 12:01.557
I don't call it any of the apps.

12:02.639 --> 12:05.403
I say, this is a phone.

12:06.485 --> 12:08.027
This is a smartphone.

12:08.047 --> 12:10.050
This is an iPhone, whatever you want to say.

12:10.571 --> 12:17.462
That is a statement of what the thing is, not what it does, but what the thing is.

12:21.088 --> 12:23.972
God is love.

12:26.136 --> 12:27.698
That's who he is.

12:28.546 --> 12:30.249
We're not describing what he does.

12:30.289 --> 12:31.511
He does, of course, love.

12:31.571 --> 12:32.592
That is an action.

12:33.073 --> 12:35.036
But this is more fundamental than that.

12:35.076 --> 12:37.319
This is more basic than that.

12:38.541 --> 12:40.364
God is love.

12:40.384 --> 12:42.527
The box in your hand is a phone.

12:42.668 --> 12:44.230
God is love.

12:45.632 --> 12:48.256
Another example.

12:48.276 --> 12:49.318
I'm 53 years old.

12:50.980 --> 12:54.345
I'm five foot six inches and a half.

12:54.586 --> 12:57.330
I'm five foot six inches and a half.

13:00.834 --> 13:08.844
I have black, but thinning hair, which when you see it in a video, you're like, why did that happen?

13:08.864 --> 13:09.845
I laugh pretty easily.

13:11.407 --> 13:14.051
Those are descriptions of who I am.

13:15.452 --> 13:19.157
Some of those might change, but they're describing me.

13:21.059 --> 13:28.168
But when I say, I am a human, that's not a description of me.

13:28.208 --> 13:29.490
That's who I am.

13:30.242 --> 13:30.903
I'm a human.

13:31.965 --> 13:35.630
When I think thoughts, I think human thoughts because I'm a human.

13:36.832 --> 13:40.678
When I speak words, I speak human words because I'm a human.

13:41.799 --> 13:46.266
I can't have non-human emotions because I'm human.

13:46.547 --> 13:51.114
The statement I am human is different from the statement that I'm five foot six and a half.

13:51.614 --> 13:53.597
The statement that I am 53 years old.

13:53.617 --> 13:59.346
Those are describing me, but when I say I am human, that is the essence of who I am.

14:00.130 --> 14:04.657
So it is when God says, God is love.

14:07.021 --> 14:09.746
It means at the core of who He is.

14:10.627 --> 14:11.328
He is love.

14:12.550 --> 14:16.336
Everything God does is loving because God is love.

14:18.340 --> 14:24.690
When God gets angry and He does get angry, it's always loving anger because God is love.

14:25.442 --> 14:31.087
When God disciplines us, it's always loving discipline because God is love.

14:32.509 --> 14:39.475
Every plan that God has for you is a loving plan because God is love.

14:40.396 --> 14:42.758
As a human, I can't think non-human thoughts.

14:43.078 --> 14:47.002
I can't say non-human words because God is love.

14:47.302 --> 14:49.525
He can't do anything that's not loving.

14:50.786 --> 14:53.408
He can't because he's love.

14:54.149 --> 14:55.410
That's who he is.

14:56.898 --> 14:59.540
That's his self-revelation to us.

15:02.423 --> 15:14.715
You see, we think the corresponding statement to, I am human is to point to God and for God to say, I am deity, which he is, he's divine, but that's not how the Bible says it.

15:16.316 --> 15:20.000
I'm human, God is love.

15:21.962 --> 15:23.343
This is how he defines himself.

15:25.465 --> 15:26.706
If you only have three words.

15:27.010 --> 15:29.033
to define God to somebody.

15:30.254 --> 15:31.055
These are your three words.

15:31.997 --> 15:32.598
Who is God?

15:33.939 --> 15:36.703
God is love.

15:38.806 --> 15:44.393
That's why if you want to ask, what is the most important thing to know about God?

15:47.217 --> 15:49.681
It's not that he's glorious, although he is.

15:51.303 --> 15:53.746
It's not that he's holy, although he is.

15:54.786 --> 16:05.705
the most important thing to know about God, the most central thing, the most basic thing, the most essential thing.

16:05.725 --> 16:08.610
God is love.

16:10.052 --> 16:13.458
He deserves glory because He's love.

16:15.101 --> 16:20.530
He is holy and set apart because He is love.

16:23.042 --> 16:27.269
Now there's more we can say about the connection between God and love from our passage.

16:28.370 --> 16:28.851
Verse seven.

16:30.974 --> 16:37.484
Dear friends, let us love one another for love comes from God.

16:41.471 --> 16:44.736
All love comes from God.

16:46.458 --> 16:51.346
Every experience of love in this world has its source in God.

16:52.834 --> 16:59.366
When a non-Christian loves their non-Christian parent, where did they get that love from?

17:01.711 --> 17:02.232
From God.

17:03.915 --> 17:08.183
When that non-Christian parent loves their non-Christian child in return, where did they get that love?

17:09.926 --> 17:10.547
From God.

17:11.249 --> 17:14.194
All love comes from God.

17:14.754 --> 17:28.892
When we say God is love, the momentous nature of this statement is that John follows this up by saying, there is no love in this world that is not ultimately sourced in God.

17:30.815 --> 17:32.176
It's a powerful declaration.

17:33.979 --> 17:36.642
If you think about it, where else would love come from?

17:41.008 --> 17:42.770
You can't medically create love.

17:44.258 --> 17:46.740
You can't edit somebody's genes to make them loving.

17:48.162 --> 17:51.205
There is no pill that you can take that will cause you to love.

17:54.288 --> 17:57.131
Science has not been able to replicate love.

17:57.551 --> 17:59.693
No one, love doesn't evolve.

18:02.396 --> 18:05.018
There are some pills you can take that will manipulate your emotions.

18:06.440 --> 18:12.786
There's some scientific things that you can do to sort of regulate how you feel, but love.

18:14.882 --> 18:19.247
to give self-sacrificially to another person, to put another person's interests above your own.

18:20.709 --> 18:21.550
Where does that come from?

18:23.993 --> 18:25.215
John says it all comes from God.

18:26.417 --> 18:32.905
When non-Christians love and Christians love any love in the world, God is the source of that love.

18:35.788 --> 18:38.752
Now, why doesn't the world recognize that God is the source of that love?

18:38.772 --> 18:43.538
Why, when you experience love, do we all not all say, oh, must be from God?

18:43.970 --> 18:45.572
Well, it's because of what we talked about last week.

18:47.513 --> 18:49.836
Because the whole world's under the control of the evil one.

18:50.756 --> 18:58.063
Because there are false prophets in this world who take love and pervert it, deceive people about it, lie about it.

18:58.904 --> 19:01.547
And so the world thinks, oh, love must be like this.

19:01.607 --> 19:03.068
Love means getting whatever you want.

19:03.108 --> 19:04.129
No, that's not what God is.

19:05.110 --> 19:05.831
That's not what love is.

19:07.893 --> 19:11.096
The world thinks, oh, no, no, I'm married to this person, but that's my soulmate.

19:11.116 --> 19:13.198
I'm going to leave this person and go be with that person.

19:13.238 --> 19:13.618
No.

19:14.178 --> 19:15.660
That's a perversion of what love is.

19:18.764 --> 19:20.387
Satan lies to us about love.

19:20.407 --> 19:22.450
He makes us think that we're unlovable.

19:22.490 --> 19:26.876
He makes us think other people are unlovable.

19:28.298 --> 19:36.569
But these are all deceptions about love, but even still in a world which is under the control of the evil one, there is still love.

19:37.571 --> 19:38.572
There's love everywhere.

19:41.055 --> 19:42.898
And John is saying, where do you think that came from?

19:44.834 --> 19:45.796
It didn't come from Satan.

19:47.839 --> 19:48.820
It's not coming from us.

19:50.242 --> 19:51.965
It's ultimately coming from God.

19:53.167 --> 19:57.834
And one of the best evidences that God exists is that there is love.

20:00.999 --> 20:06.488
There's a third thing to say about how God and love are so intimately connected, verse 12.

20:08.030 --> 20:12.978
No one has ever seen God, but if we love one another, God lives in us.

20:14.018 --> 20:16.521
And his love is made complete in us, verse 16.

20:17.542 --> 20:21.606
And so we know and rely on the love God has for us.

20:22.167 --> 20:27.733
God is love, whoever lives in love lives in God and God in them.

20:28.874 --> 20:32.538
So closely connected are God and love.

20:33.779 --> 20:40.947
That if you and I live lives of love, the only explanation is God is living in us.

20:41.768 --> 20:43.730
Because God is the source of all love.

20:44.610 --> 20:55.465
that when you experience love, when you give love, when you live a life of love, God is the one who is in you doing these things.

20:56.527 --> 21:00.472
Not does that mean that every non-Christian who loves somebody must have God in them?

21:02.054 --> 21:07.442
No one says you're living a life of love, that we're loving one another, we're loving our enemies.

21:07.874 --> 21:09.696
We're loving those who are not like us.

21:09.736 --> 21:11.838
We are loving those that seem to be unlovable.

21:11.858 --> 21:21.147
We're loving at times when you don't feel, but the only explanation, if you are living a life of love, the only explanation is that God is in you doing these things.

21:25.031 --> 21:36.722
It is unambiguous, so closely connected, our God and love, that if you are living out a life of love, if you are loving God,

21:37.154 --> 21:38.055
and loving your neighbor.

21:39.156 --> 21:42.160
The only possible explanation is that God is in you.

21:45.644 --> 21:46.225
God is love.

21:47.747 --> 21:52.793
Let me say three invitations from this truth for us today.

21:55.236 --> 22:06.290
First, as we enter the Christmas season, we're going to talk more next week about how the fullest expression of God's love to us is Him

22:06.498 --> 22:12.065
coming in the person of Jesus to be born as a human, to die on a cross for our sins.

22:12.766 --> 22:14.788
That is the fullest expression of God's love.

22:15.149 --> 22:18.453
But here's the invitation to all of us this morning.

22:19.674 --> 22:20.736
And the invitation is this.

22:22.438 --> 22:29.466
There is no more momentous truth in all the Bible than the declaration that God has left.

22:30.728 --> 22:35.634
The invitation is you and I would do well to spend time today

22:36.514 --> 22:40.460
tomorrow, this week, thinking about the truth.

22:40.841 --> 22:43.025
God is love.

22:44.226 --> 22:49.896
I would love for you to go from this place and think about the fact love is not an attribute of God.

22:50.016 --> 22:51.699
It's the essence of who he is.

22:51.979 --> 23:00.994
Everything he does, everything he does, everything he does is loving because he is love.

23:01.014 --> 23:03.698
He cannot not be loving.

23:04.866 --> 23:06.769
That's a truth worth pondering.

23:07.009 --> 23:08.832
That is a truth worth thinking about.

23:09.694 --> 23:12.558
If you're of the age where you're like, well, it's tough to memorize verses these days.

23:12.758 --> 23:14.281
This is a good one to memorize.

23:14.701 --> 23:16.624
God is love.

23:17.205 --> 23:18.047
Say it out loud with me.

23:18.107 --> 23:20.370
God is love.

23:20.671 --> 23:22.073
You've all memorized a verse of the Bible.

23:22.113 --> 23:22.533
Good job.

23:25.518 --> 23:26.500
But it's worth thinking about.

23:28.943 --> 23:33.170
It's the simplest statement on the earth, but it's the most profound.

23:34.786 --> 23:38.912
I want you to spend time thinking about because God is love.

23:41.135 --> 23:43.818
You see, some of us think that his default mode is anger.

23:44.239 --> 23:45.861
It can't be that.

23:47.864 --> 23:50.768
We spend a lot of our time thinking that he's angry with us.

23:51.409 --> 23:52.310
God does get angry.

23:52.911 --> 23:54.854
Please, he absolutely gets angry.

23:56.035 --> 23:58.959
But in his angriest moment, guess what?

24:00.321 --> 24:01.042
God is love.

24:02.562 --> 24:04.304
He cannot lash out.

24:04.585 --> 24:06.147
He cannot react.

24:06.167 --> 24:09.171
He cannot act in that way because God is love.

24:09.191 --> 24:10.753
That's why He's telling us who He is.

24:10.993 --> 24:16.261
He says, I want you to understand everything I do is based in love.

24:16.341 --> 24:18.043
It is sourced in love.

24:18.063 --> 24:22.489
All things come from love because God is love.

24:23.871 --> 24:30.079
Some of us are convinced that God can be bothered with us, that He's on the bigger things.

24:30.099 --> 24:32.082
Like He's got a whole world to run and who are we?

24:32.994 --> 24:36.399
And why could our little problems amount to any hill of beans in God's world?

24:39.062 --> 24:42.547
But I want you to meditate on this because that can't possibly be the case.

24:43.408 --> 24:43.829
Why not?

24:45.131 --> 24:46.232
Because God is love.

24:47.174 --> 24:48.576
God cannot ignore you.

24:49.497 --> 24:52.601
God cannot not care about the things you care about.

24:52.641 --> 24:53.042
Why?

24:54.524 --> 24:55.746
Because God is love.

24:56.647 --> 24:57.668
Everything He does.

24:58.149 --> 25:01.874
Every action that He takes, it's in love.

25:03.522 --> 25:07.907
When God disciplines us, it is loving discipline.

25:08.187 --> 25:08.468
Why?

25:10.230 --> 25:11.131
Because God is love.

25:13.433 --> 25:18.259
You could spend the rest of your life and the rest of eternity pondering this phrase.

25:21.222 --> 25:27.749
And I'm just going to tell you of all of the passages in the Bible, of all of the thoughts in the Bible that you could think.

25:29.151 --> 25:30.712
The most foundational is Jesus' Lord.

25:30.732 --> 25:32.114
We're going to get to that one in just a second.

25:34.082 --> 25:37.727
But there is no other statement that will pay as much fruit.

25:39.009 --> 25:40.971
There's many dividends.

25:40.991 --> 25:46.979
As if you and I keep wrestling with, God explained to me what it means that you are love.

25:48.842 --> 25:50.824
Help me to realize and grasp this.

25:51.145 --> 26:00.097
There's a passage in Ephesians that says that we might together with all the saints grasp the height and the breadth and the width and the depth of God's love.

26:00.117 --> 26:01.138
And when you grasp,

26:01.218 --> 26:03.942
That you are filled to the fullness of God.

26:04.182 --> 26:13.416
There is no better activity that you can ever do than spend your time meditating on what it means that God is love.

26:16.561 --> 26:18.043
You are loved by God.

26:18.945 --> 26:23.111
There is nothing you can do to earn love from God because God is love.

26:24.793 --> 26:26.376
There is no end to what you can do with this.

26:28.018 --> 26:30.642
So my encouragement to you, invitation number one.

26:31.330 --> 26:33.853
spend whatever time you've got this week.

26:35.055 --> 26:37.878
Just thinking about the fact, God is love.

26:40.622 --> 26:42.524
He's not loving, of course he is.

26:43.665 --> 26:44.747
God is love.

26:45.888 --> 26:47.150
That's the essence of he is, okay?

26:47.170 --> 26:48.011
Invitation number two.

26:49.653 --> 26:54.619
This has to do with the Jesus' Lord idea, and the invitation goes especially to those who are not yet Christians.

26:57.122 --> 27:00.146
If you've experienced any love in this world,

27:01.570 --> 27:10.643
if your dog loves you, if you love nature, if you have a friend in your life who has shown you love.

27:12.726 --> 27:17.112
The question to ask is where did that love come from?

27:17.152 --> 27:22.219
Did the little doggy wake up one day and decide to be a loving dog?

27:23.842 --> 27:27.026
Did the trees create the love that you're experiencing?

27:28.130 --> 27:34.219
Is your friend so wonderful and so perfect that they are the source of love in your life?

27:35.642 --> 27:36.583
The answer is no.

27:37.004 --> 27:46.558
All of these things, the love that the dog has for you and that you have for the dog, the love that you experience in nature, the love that we experience from friends, all of this are signs.

27:46.638 --> 27:52.087
All of these are signs pointing us to the God who is the source of all those things.

27:52.888 --> 27:54.250
And here is the invitation.

27:54.811 --> 27:56.754
If you have been loved by a dog,

27:57.474 --> 28:09.726
If you have been loved or loved being in nature, if you have been loved by a friend, the invitation is God is inviting you to come and discover Him because He is love.

28:12.489 --> 28:24.701
And if you've had any shadow of love, no matter how sort of tainted or faint or confusing, Satan cannot stop love from existing in this world.

28:24.741 --> 28:25.522
He perverts it.

28:26.178 --> 28:27.359
He deceives us about it.

28:27.920 --> 28:29.021
He tries to hinder it.

28:30.503 --> 28:32.044
But God is way too powerful.

28:33.566 --> 28:43.857
And the invitation is, if you've had any love in your life, why not come to know the one who is the source of love?

28:45.239 --> 28:47.081
Look, you might think he's going to be angry.

28:47.481 --> 28:48.402
He can't be.

28:49.543 --> 28:51.265
You might think he's going to reject me.

28:51.626 --> 28:53.247
He absolutely can't.

28:54.128 --> 28:55.730
Not just that he won't.

28:56.066 --> 28:58.630
He can't because he's love.

29:01.233 --> 29:03.677
I mean, love is, is that not what brings joy in this world?

29:06.060 --> 29:10.206
And the invitation is come and meet the one who is love.

29:11.588 --> 29:17.437
Come and meet the one who loved you enough to send his son so that you might know that he is love.

29:19.119 --> 29:23.986
Every piece of love we've experienced in this world is just an appetizer.

29:25.826 --> 29:29.410
pointing us to the source of all love, and it's God.

29:30.332 --> 29:43.868
So the second invitation is, come and meet Him, come and know Him, come and experience real love, pure love, sublime love, love that will love you more than you could ever possibly imagine.

29:47.673 --> 29:52.018
The third invitation is for all of us this holiday season.

29:54.242 --> 30:08.340
If you would like more of God in your life, and if you would like more of God in your holidays, the invitation is to choose to love others during the season.

30:09.522 --> 30:15.790
The crazy thing about Christmas is this expression of God's love, but we often turn it into a way to love ourselves.

30:16.871 --> 30:18.653
We think, well, these are the presents I want.

30:19.875 --> 30:22.258
These are the family experiences I want to have.

30:22.882 --> 30:25.045
This is how I want Christmas day to go.

30:25.085 --> 30:35.818
As aside, let me just say that God loves each one of us too much to let our holiday plans turn out exactly the way we want them to turn out.

30:39.502 --> 30:46.771
The invitation here is not to think about, well, how can I make sure that these holidays go the way I want them to go?

30:48.313 --> 30:52.498
You might succeed at that, you probably won't, but in either case,

30:52.898 --> 30:55.502
God won't be present.

30:55.522 --> 31:03.054
But if instead this holiday season, you simply say to God, okay, God, not my will, but yours be done.

31:04.736 --> 31:07.040
When you say to others, how can I serve you?

31:07.200 --> 31:07.961
How can I love you?

31:08.282 --> 31:09.223
What can I do for others?

31:09.363 --> 31:11.527
It is better to give than to receive.

31:12.909 --> 31:18.898
The invitation this holiday season is to remember God is love.

31:19.970 --> 31:26.700
When we choose to love others, God dwells in us and we experience God.

31:27.661 --> 31:29.825
Maybe right now you're feeling distant from God.

31:30.225 --> 31:32.929
Maybe you're feeling like I haven't heard from God in a long time.

31:33.250 --> 31:36.574
Maybe you're thinking it feels like I don't know what God is up to.

31:36.615 --> 31:37.997
Here's the invitation.

31:38.858 --> 31:44.566
If you want God tangibly present in your life, choose to love others.

31:45.588 --> 31:47.130
And there's no better time to do this.

31:48.172 --> 31:49.874
No harder time to do this.

31:50.338 --> 31:52.441
than during the holiday season.

31:52.461 --> 31:53.663
These are the three invitations.

31:54.544 --> 31:59.631
Spend time thinking, meditating, memorizing God is love.

31:59.651 --> 32:10.566
If you're not yet a Christian, accept the fact that in every act of love you experience, God is inviting you to come and meet the source of all of that love.

32:10.586 --> 32:19.538
And during the holiday season, if you want more of God present in your life, choose to love others as he's loved us.

32:21.858 --> 32:25.162
Lord willing, I'll get to preach at Calvary for many more years in the future.

32:26.404 --> 32:33.753
But I will never again be able to say in this same sort of way our text this morning is the most momentous truth in the Bible.

32:35.115 --> 32:37.458
There are other really, really powerful things to say.

32:39.300 --> 32:49.874
But the most fundamental, the most powerful, the most definitive statement is God is love.

